{"qid": "Q1263806", "name": "Duduka da Fonseca", "match_basis": "qid", "ch_id": "96688", "ch_uri": "http://data.carnegiehall.org/names/96688", "birth": "1951", "death": null, "description": "Brazilian musician", "abstract": "Duduka Da Fonseca, born Eduardo Moreira Da Fonseca (Rio de Janeiro, March 31, 1951) is a Brazilian jazz drummer who is a founding member of Trio da Paz with Romero Lubambo and Nilson Matta. He leads the Duduka da Fonseca Trio, with David Feldman and Guto Wirtti.", "wp_title": "Duduka Da Fonseca", "image": "img/p/Q1263806.jpg", "is_interviewee": false, "lj_docs": 1, "lj_mentions": 1, "lj_node": "wd:Q1263806", "interviews": [], "concerts": [{"id": "27872", "date": "1997-03-06", "label": "Carnegie Hall Jazz Band: An Evening of Brazilian Jazz", "venue": "Isaac Stern Auditorium / Ronald O. Perelman Stage", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Brigas Nunca Mais", "c": "Antônio Carlos Jobim", "w": "45823"}, {"t": "Dom Joaquim Braga", "c": "Claudio Roditi", "w": "58937"}, {"t": "The Monster and the Flower", "c": "Claudio Roditi", "w": "50579"}]}, {"id": "52758", "date": "2014-04-05", "label": "Trio da Paz", "venue": "Zankel Hall", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "56510", "date": "2015-11-28", "label": "Rio 65 Trio 50th Anniversary Concert", "venue": "Zankel Hall", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Temátrio", "c": "Dom Salvador", "w": "95201"}, {"t": "Clauditi", "c": "Dom Salvador", "w": "95208"}, {"t": "Azul Contente", "c": "Walter Santos", "w": "95210"}, {"t": "Depois da Chuva", "c": "Dom Salvador", "w": "95204"}, {"t": "Farjuto", "c": "Dom Salvador", "w": "95205"}, {"t": "Tem Dó", "c": "Baden Powell", "w": "95211"}, {"t": "Desafinado", "c": "Antônio Carlos Jobim", "w": "59211"}, {"t": "Mau Mau", "c": "Art Farmer", "w": "95209"}, {"t": "Meu Fraco é Café Forte", "c": "Dom Salvador", "w": "95202"}, {"t": "Gafieira", "c": "Dom Salvador", "w": "95203"}, {"t": "Unification", "c": "Dom Salvador", "w": "95207"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Kenny Barron", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "Then I decided to put together a group with Trio de Paz. They knew a percussionist named Valtinho... Duduka da Fonseca, “This rhythm comes from the north of Brazil.” So I learned more than I knew.", "doc_title": "Kenny Barron — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Barron-Kenny/Barron_Kenny_Transcript.pdf"}]}